3.4. Real-Time Adjustments Between Frames
The AI system doesn’t just blindly move from Frame A to Frame B. It continuously monitors for changes in the environment that might affect the INTENT. If an obstacle or anomaly is detected, the AI dynamically adjusts:

New Reality Frames: If an obstacle is detected, the AI immediately recalculates a new desired reality frame, adjusting the patrol route to avoid the obstacle while staying within the geoboundary.
Behavioral Changes: If the INTENT changes (e.g., the patrol is complete, or the robot is relieved), the AI switches to a new behavior (e.g., stand by, return to base).
